  "prompt": "What were the major events that happened in 2005?",
  "response": "Certainly! Many significant events took place in 2005 across various domains, including politics, natural disasters, scientific advancements, and popular culture. Here are some of the notable events:\n\n1. **Natural Disasters:**\n   - **Hurricane Katrina:** One of the deadliest and costliest hurricanes in U.S. history struck the Gulf Coast in August, devastating New Orleans and surrounding areas. Over 1,800 people died, and millions were affected.\n   - **Pakistan Earthquake:** A massive earthquake occurred in northern Pakistan on October 8, resulting in around 86,000 deaths and causing widespread destruction.\n\n2. **Politics:**\n   - **Angela Merkel Becomes Chancellor:** Angela Merkel became the first female Chancellor of Germany in November after the federal election.\n   - **Pope Benedict XVI:** Cardinal Joseph Ratzinger was elected as Pope Benedict XVI on April 19, following the death of Pope John Paul II.\n   - **Kyoto Protocol:** The Kyoto Protocol aimed at combating global warming officially came into effect on February 16 after Russia ratified the treaty in 2004.\n\n3. **Science and Technology:**\n   - **Discovery of Eris:** The dwarf planet Eris was discovered, leading to further discussions on the definitions of planets and dwarf planets.\n   - **YouTube Launch:** YouTube was created in February 2005, revolutionizing how people share and consume videos online.\n\n4. **Notable Deaths:**\n   - **Pope John Paul II:** Pope John Paul II passed away on April 2 after serving as Pope since 1978.\n   - **Rosa Parks:** The civil rights icon Rosa Parks died on October 24.\n\n5. **Pop Culture:**\n   - **Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith:** Released in May, this film concluded the Star Wars prequel trilogy and was a major box office event.\n   - **Live 8 Concerts:** Organized by Bob Geldof, the Live 8 concerts were held on July 2 across major cities to raise awareness about global poverty ahead of the G8 summit.\n\n6. **Economy:**\n   - **Oil Prices:** Crude oil prices hit unprecedented highs during 2005, affecting global economies.\n\nThese events had a significant impact on global affairs and have been remembered for their historical importance.",
